  73. module Make(Ord: OrderedType) =
  74.   struct
  75. ‌    type elt = Ord.t
  76. ‌    type t = Empty | Node of {l:t; v:elt; r:t; h:int}

  78.     (* Sets are represented by balanced binary trees (the heights of the
  79.        children differ by at most 2 *)

  81. ‌    let height = function
  82.         Empty -> 0
  83.       | Node {h} -> h

  85.     (* Creates a new node with left son l, value v and right son r.
  86.        We must have all elements of l < v < all elements of r.
  87.        l and r must be balanced and | height l - height r | <= 2.
  88.        Inline expansion of height for better speed. *)

  90. ‌    let create l v r =
  91.       let hl = match l with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  92.       let hr = match r with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  93.       Node{l; v; r; h=(if hl >= hr then hl + 1 else hr + 1)}

  95.     (* Same as create, but performs one step of rebalancing if necessary.
  96.        Assumes l and r balanced and | height l - height r | <= 3.
  97.        Inline expansion of create for better speed in the most frequent case
  98.        where no rebalancing is required. *)

  100. ‌    let bal l v r =
  101.       let hl = match l with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  102.       let hr = match r with Empty -> 0 | Node {h} -> h in
  103.       if hl > hr + 2 then begin
  104.         match l with
  105.           Empty -> invalid_arg "Set.bal"
  106.         | Node{l=ll; v=lv; r=lr} ->
  107.             if height ll >= height lr then
  108.               create ll lv (create lr v r)
  109.             else begin
  110.               match lr with
  111.                 Empty -> invalid_arg "Set.bal"
  112.               | Node{l=lrl; v=lrv; r=lrr}->
  113.                   create (create ll lv lrl) lrv (create lrr v r)
  114.             end
  115.       end else if hr > hl + 2 then begin
  116.         match r with
  117.           Empty -> invalid_arg "Set.bal"
  118.         | Node{l=rl; v=rv; r=rr} ->
  119.             if height rr >= height rl then
  120.               create (create l v rl) rv rr
  121.             else begin
  122.               match rl with
  123.                 Empty -> invalid_arg "Set.bal"
  124.               | Node{l=rll; v=rlv; r=rlr} ->
  125.                   create (create l v rll) rlv (create rlr rv rr)
  126.             end
  127.       end else
  128.         Node{l; v; r; h=(if hl >= hr then hl + 1 else hr + 1)}

  130.     (* Insertion of one element *)

  132. ‌    let rec add x = function
  133.         Empty -> Node{l=Empty; v=x; r=Empty; h=1}
  134.       | Node{l; v; r} as t ->
  135.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  136.           if c = 0 then t else
  137.           if c < 0 then
  138.             let ll = add x l in
  139.             if l == ll then t else bal ll v r
  140.           else
  141.             let rr = add x r in
  142.             if r == rr then t else bal l v rr

  144. ‌    let singleton x = Node{l=Empty; v=x; r=Empty; h=1}

  146.     (* Beware: those two functions assume that the added v is *strictly*
  147.        smaller (or bigger) than all the present elements in the tree; it
  148.        does not test for equality with the current min (or max) element.
  149.        Indeed, they are only used during the "join" operation which
  150.        respects this precondition.
  151.     *)

  153. ‌    let rec add_min_element x = function
  154.       | Empty -> singleton x
  155.       | Node {l; v; r} ->
  156.         bal (add_min_element x l) v r

  158. ‌    let rec add_max_element x = function
  159.       | Empty -> singleton x
  160.       | Node {l; v; r} ->
  161.         bal l v (add_max_element x r)

  163.     (* Same as create and bal, but no assumptions are made on the
  164.        relative heights of l and r. *)

  166. ‌    let rec join l v r =
  167.       match (l, r) with
  168.         (Empty, _) -> add_min_element v r
  169.       | (_, Empty) -> add_max_element v l
  170.       | (Node{l=ll; v=lv; r=lr; h=lh}, Node{l=rl; v=rv; r=rr; h=rh}) ->
  171.           if lh > rh + 2 then bal ll lv (join lr v r) else
  172.           if rh > lh + 2 then bal (join l v rl) rv rr else
  173.           create l v r

  175.     (* Smallest and greatest element of a set *)

  177. ‌    let rec min_elt = function
  178.         Empty -> raise Not_found
  179.       | Node{l=Empty; v} -> v
  180.       | Node{l} -> min_elt l

  182. ‌    let rec min_elt_opt = function
  183.         Empty -> None
  184.       | Node{l=Empty; v} -> Some v
  185.       | Node{l} -> min_elt_opt l

  187. ‌    let rec max_elt = function
  188.         Empty -> raise Not_found
  189.       | Node{v; r=Empty} -> v
  190.       | Node{r} -> max_elt r

  192. ‌    let rec max_elt_opt = function
  193.         Empty -> None
  194.       | Node{v; r=Empty} -> Some v
  195.       | Node{r} -> max_elt_opt r

  197.     (* Remove the smallest element of the given set *)

  199. ‌    let rec remove_min_elt = function
  200.         Empty -> invalid_arg "Set.remove_min_elt"
  201.       | Node{l=Empty; r} -> r
  202.       | Node{l; v; r} -> bal (remove_min_elt l) v r

  204.     (* Merge two trees l and r into one.
  205.        All elements of l must precede the elements of r.
  206.        Assume | height l - height r | <= 2. *)

  208. ‌    let merge t1 t2 =
  209.       match (t1, t2) with
  210.         (Empty, t) -> t
  211.       | (t, Empty) -> t
  212.       | (_, _) -> bal t1 (min_elt t2) (remove_min_elt t2)

  214.     (* Merge two trees l and r into one.
  215.        All elements of l must precede the elements of r.
  216.        No assumption on the heights of l and r. *)

  218. ‌    let concat t1 t2 =
  219.       match (t1, t2) with
  220.         (Empty, t) -> t
  221.       | (t, Empty) -> t
  222.       | (_, _) -> join t1 (min_elt t2) (remove_min_elt t2)

  224.     (* Splitting.  split x s returns a triple (l, present, r) where
  225.         - l is the set of elements of s that are < x
  226.         - r is the set of elements of s that are > x
  227.         - present is false if s contains no element equal to x,
  228.           or true if s contains an element equal to x. *)

  230. ‌    let rec split x = function
  231.         Empty ->
  232.           (Empty, false, Empty)
  233.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  234.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  235.           if c = 0 then (l, true, r)
  236.           else if c < 0 then
  237.             let (ll, pres, rl) = split x l in (ll, pres, join rl v r)
  238.           else
  239.             let (lr, pres, rr) = split x r in (join l v lr, pres, rr)

  241.     (* Implementation of the set operations *)

  243. ‌    let empty = Empty

  245. ‌    let is_empty = function Empty -> true | _ -> false

  247. ‌    let rec mem x = function
  248.         Empty -> false
  249.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  250.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  251.           c = 0 || mem x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  253. ‌    let rec remove x = function
  254.         Empty -> Empty
  255.       | (Node{l; v; r} as t) ->
  256.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  257.           if c = 0 then merge l r
  258.           else
  259.             if c < 0 then
  260.               let ll = remove x l in
  261.               if l == ll then t
  262.               else bal ll v r
  263.             else
  264.               let rr = remove x r in
  265.               if r == rr then t
  266.               else bal l v rr

  268. ‌    let rec union s1 s2 =
  269.       match (s1, s2) with
  270.         (Empty, t2) -> t2
  271.       | (t1, Empty) -> t1
  272.       | (Node{l=l1; v=v1; r=r1; h=h1}, Node{l=l2; v=v2; r=r2; h=h2}) ->
  273.           if h1 >= h2 then
  274.             if h2 = 1 then add v2 s1 else begin
  275.               let (l2, _, r2) = split v1 s2 in
  276.               join (union l1 l2) v1 (union r1 r2)
  277.             end
  278.           else
  279.             if h1 = 1 then add v1 s2 else begin
  280.               let (l1, _, r1) = split v2 s1 in
  281.               join (union l1 l2) v2 (union r1 r2)
  282.             end

  284.     let rec inter s1 s2 =
  285.       match (s1, s2) with
  286.         (Empty, _) -> Empty
  287.       | (_, Empty) -> Empty
  288.       | (Node{l=l1; v=v1; r=r1}, t2) ->
  289.           match split v1 t2 with
  290.             (l2, false, r2) ->
  291.               concat (inter l1 l2) (inter r1 r2)
  292.           | (l2, true, r2) ->
  293.               join (inter l1 l2) v1 (inter r1 r2)

  295.     (* Same as split, but compute the left and right subtrees
  296.        only if the pivot element is not in the set.  The right subtree
  297.        is computed on demand. *)

  299. ‌    type split_bis =
  300.       | Found
  301.       | NotFound of t * (unit -> t)

  303. ‌    let rec split_bis x = function
  304.         Empty ->
  305.           NotFound (Empty, (fun () -> Empty))
  306.       | Node{l; v; r; _} ->
  307.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  308.           if c = 0 then Found
  309.           else if c < 0 then
  310.             match split_bis x l with
  311.             | Found -> Found
  312.             | NotFound (ll, rl) -> NotFound (ll, (fun () -> join (rl ()) v r))
  313.           else
  314.             match split_bis x r with
  315.             | Found -> Found
  316.             | NotFound (lr, rr) -> NotFound (join l v lr, rr)

  318. ‌    let rec disjoint s1 s2 =
  319.       match (s1, s2) with
  320.         (Empty, _) | (_, Empty) -> true
  321.       | (Node{l=l1; v=v1; r=r1}, t2) ->
  322.           if s1 == s2 then false
  323.           else match split_bis v1 t2 with
  324.               NotFound(l2, r2) -> disjoint l1 l2 && disjoint r1 (r2 ())
  325.             | Found -> false

  327. ‌    let rec diff s1 s2 =
  328.       match (s1, s2) with
  329.         (Empty, _) -> Empty
  330.       | (t1, Empty) -> t1
  331.       | (Node{l=l1; v=v1; r=r1}, t2) ->
  332.           match split v1 t2 with
  333.             (l2, false, r2) ->
  334.               join (diff l1 l2) v1 (diff r1 r2)
  335.           | (l2, true, r2) ->
  336.               concat (diff l1 l2) (diff r1 r2)

  338. ‌    type enumeration = End | More of elt * t * enumeration

  340. ‌    let rec cons_enum s e =
  341.       match s with
  342.         Empty -> e
  343.       | Node{l; v; r} -> cons_enum l (More(v, r, e))

  345. ‌    let rec compare_aux e1 e2 =
  346.         match (e1, e2) with
  347.         (End, End) -> 0
  348.       | (End, _)  -> -1
  349.       | (_, End) -> 1
  350.       | (More(v1, r1, e1), More(v2, r2, e2)) ->
  351.           let c = Ord.compare v1 v2 in
  352.           if c <> 0
  353.           then c
  354.           else compare_aux (cons_enum r1 e1) (cons_enum r2 e2)

  356. ‌    let compare s1 s2 =
  357.       compare_aux (cons_enum s1 End) (cons_enum s2 End)

  359. ‌    let equal s1 s2 =
  360.       compare s1 s2 = 0

  362. ‌    let rec subset s1 s2 =
  363.       match (s1, s2) with
  364.         Empty, _ ->
  365.           true
  366.       | _, Empty ->
  367.           false
  368.       | Node {l=l1; v=v1; r=r1}, (Node {l=l2; v=v2; r=r2} as t2) ->
  369.           let c = Ord.compare v1 v2 in
  370.           if c = 0 then
  371.             subset l1 l2 && subset r1 r2
  372.           else if c < 0 then
  373.             subset (Node {l=l1; v=v1; r=Empty; h=0}) l2 && subset r1 t2
  374.           else
  375.             subset (Node {l=Empty; v=v1; r=r1; h=0}) r2 && subset l1 t2

  377. ‌    let rec iter f = function
  378.         Empty -> ()
  379.       | Node{l; v; r} -> iter f l; f v; iter f r

  381. ‌    let rec fold f s accu =
  382.       match s with
  383.         Empty -> accu
  384.       | Node{l; v; r} -> fold f r (f v (fold f l accu))

  386. ‌    let rec for_all p = function
  387.         Empty -> true
  388.       | Node{l; v; r} -> p v && for_all p l && for_all p r

  390. ‌    let rec exists p = function
  391.         Empty -> false
  392.       | Node{l; v; r} -> p v || exists p l || exists p r

  394. ‌    let rec filter p = function
  395.         Empty -> Empty
  396.       | (Node{l; v; r}) as t ->
  397.           (* call [p] in the expected left-to-right order *)
  398.           let l' = filter p l in
  399.           let pv = p v in
  400.           let r' = filter p r in
  401.           if pv then
  402.             if l==l' && r==r' then t else join l' v r'
  403.           else concat l' r'

  405. ‌    let rec partition p = function
  406.         Empty -> (Empty, Empty)
  407.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  408.           (* call [p] in the expected left-to-right order *)
  409.           let (lt, lf) = partition p l in
  410.           let pv = p v in
  411.           let (rt, rf) = partition p r in
  412.           if pv
  413.           then (join lt v rt, concat lf rf)
  414.           else (concat lt rt, join lf v rf)

  416. ‌    let rec cardinal = function
  417.         Empty -> 0
  418.       | Node{l; r} -> cardinal l + 1 + cardinal r

  420. ‌    let rec elements_aux accu = function
  421.         Empty -> accu
  422.       | Node{l; v; r} -> elements_aux (v :: elements_aux accu r) l

  424. ‌    let elements s =
  425.       elements_aux [] s

  427. ‌    let choose = min_elt

  429. ‌    let choose_opt = min_elt_opt

  431. ‌    let rec find x = function
  432.         Empty -> raise Not_found
  433.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  434.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  435.           if c = 0 then v
  436.           else find x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  438. ‌    let rec find_first_aux v0 f = function
  439.         Empty ->
  440.           v0
  441.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  442.           if f v then
  443.             find_first_aux v f l
  444.           else
  445.             find_first_aux v0 f r

  447. ‌    let rec find_first f = function
  448.         Empty ->
  449.           raise Not_found
  450.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  451.           if f v then
  452.             find_first_aux v f l
  453.           else
  454.             find_first f r

  456. ‌    let rec find_first_opt_aux v0 f = function
  457.         Empty ->
  458.           Some v0
  459.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  460.           if f v then
  461.             find_first_opt_aux v f l
  462.           else
  463.             find_first_opt_aux v0 f r

  465. ‌    let rec find_first_opt f = function
  466.         Empty ->
  467.           None
  468.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  469.           if f v then
  470.             find_first_opt_aux v f l
  471.           else
  472.             find_first_opt f r

  474. ‌    let rec find_last_aux v0 f = function
  475.         Empty ->
  476.           v0
  477.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  478.           if f v then
  479.             find_last_aux v f r
  480.           else
  481.             find_last_aux v0 f l

  483. ‌    let rec find_last f = function
  484.         Empty ->
  485.           raise Not_found
  486.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  487.           if f v then
  488.             find_last_aux v f r
  489.           else
  490.             find_last f l

  492. ‌    let rec find_last_opt_aux v0 f = function
  493.         Empty ->
  494.           Some v0
  495.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  496.           if f v then
  497.             find_last_opt_aux v f r
  498.           else
  499.             find_last_opt_aux v0 f l

  501. ‌    let rec find_last_opt f = function
  502.         Empty ->
  503.           None
  504.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  505.           if f v then
  506.             find_last_opt_aux v f r
  507.           else
  508.             find_last_opt f l

  510. ‌    let rec find_opt x = function
  511.         Empty -> None
  512.       | Node{l; v; r} ->
  513.           let c = Ord.compare x v in
  514.           if c = 0 then Some v
  515.           else find_opt x (if c < 0 then l else r)

  517. ‌    let try_join l v r =
  518.       (* [join l v r] can only be called when (elements of l < v <
  519.          elements of r); use [try_join l v r] when this property may
  520.          not hold, but you hope it does hold in the common case *)
  521.       if (l = Empty || Ord.compare (max_elt l) v < 0)
  522.       && (r = Empty || Ord.compare v (min_elt r) < 0)
  523.       then join l v r
  524.       else union l (add v r)

  526. ‌    let rec map f = function
  527.       | Empty -> Empty
  528.       | Node{l; v; r} as t ->
  529.          (* enforce left-to-right evaluation order *)
  530.          let l' = map f l in
  531.          let v' = f v in
  532.          let r' = map f r in
  533.          if l == l' && v == v' && r == r' then t
  534.          else try_join l' v' r'

  536. ‌    let try_concat t1 t2 =
  537.       match (t1, t2) with
  538.         (Empty, t) -> t
  539.       | (t, Empty) -> t
  540.       | (_, _) -> try_join t1 (min_elt t2) (remove_min_elt t2)

  542. ‌    let rec filter_map f = function
  543.       | Empty -> Empty
  544.       | Node{l; v; r} as t ->
  545.          (* enforce left-to-right evaluation order *)
  546.          let l' = filter_map f l in
  547.          let v' = f v in
  548.          let r' = filter_map f r in
  549.          begin match v' with
  550.            | Some v' ->
  551.               if l == l' && v == v' && r == r' then t
  552.               else try_join l' v' r'
  553.            | None ->
  554.               try_concat l' r'
  555.          end

  557.     let of_sorted_list l =
  558.       let rec sub n l =
  559.         match n, l with
  560.         | 0, l -> Empty, l
  561.         | 1, x0 :: l -> Node {l=Empty; v=x0; r=Empty; h=1}, l
  562.         | 2, x0 :: x1 :: l ->
  563.             Node{l=Node{l=Empty; v=x0; r=Empty; h=1}; v=x1; r=Empty; h=2}, l
  564.         | 3, x0 :: x1 :: x2 :: l ->
  565.             Node{l=Node{l=Empty; v=x0; r=Empty; h=1}; v=x1;
  566.                  r=Node{l=Empty; v=x2; r=Empty; h=1}; h=2}, l
  567.         | n, l ->
  568.           let nl = n / 2 in
  569.           let left, l = sub nl l in
  570.           match l with
  571.           | [] -> assert false
  572.           | mid :: l ->
  573.             let right, l = sub (n - nl - 1) l in
  574.             create left mid right, l
  575.       in
  576.       fst (sub (List.length l) l)

  578. ‌    let to_list = elements

  580. ‌    let of_list l =
  581.       match l with
  582.       | [] -> empty
  583.       | [x0] -> singleton x0
  584.       | [x0; x1] -> add x1 (singleton x0)
  585.       | [x0; x1; x2] -> add x2 (add x1 (singleton x0))
  586.       | [x0; x1; x2; x3] -> add x3 (add x2 (add x1 (singleton x0)))
  587.       | [x0; x1; x2; x3; x4] -> add x4 (add x3 (add x2 (add x1 (singleton x0))))
  588.       | _ -> of_sorted_list (List.sort_uniq Ord.compare l)

  590. ‌    let add_seq i m =
  591.       Seq.fold_left (fun s x -> add x s) m i

  593.     let of_seq i = add_seq i empty

  595.     let rec seq_of_enum_ c () = match c with
  596.       | End -> Seq.Nil
  597.       | More (x, t, rest) -> Seq.Cons (x, seq_of_enum_ (cons_enum t rest))

  599. ‌    let to_seq c = seq_of_enum_ (cons_enum c End)

  601. ‌    let rec snoc_enum s e =
  602.       match s with
  603.         Empty -> e
  604.       | Node{l; v; r} -> snoc_enum r (More(v, l, e))

  606. ‌    let rec rev_seq_of_enum_ c () = match c with
  607.       | End -> Seq.Nil
  608.       | More (x, t, rest) -> Seq.Cons (x, rev_seq_of_enum_ (snoc_enum t rest))

  610. ‌    let to_rev_seq c = rev_seq_of_enum_ (snoc_enum c End)

  612. ‌    let to_seq_from low s =
  613.       let rec aux low s c = match s with
  614.         | Empty -> c
  615.         | Node {l; r; v; _} ->
  616.             begin match Ord.compare v low with
  617.               | 0 -> More (v, r, c)
  618.               | n when n<0 -> aux low r c
  619.               | _ -> aux low l (More (v, r, c))
  620.             end
  621.       in
  622.       seq_of_enum_ (aux low s End)
  623.   end
